<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="49" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1431,2017]" pageId="2" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,321,1631,1657]" pageId="2" pageNumber="49">Variation.</emphasis>
The four male 
<typeStatus box="[515,627,1631,1657]" pageId="2" pageNumber="49">paratypes</typeStatus>
range from 
<quantity box="[773,944,1631,1657]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.85" metricValueMax="4.2" metricValueMin="3.5" pageId="2" pageNumber="49" unit="mm" value="3.85" valueMax="4.2" valueMin="3.5">3.50–4.20 mm</quantity>
in length. On two of them the blue color on the pronotum is restricted to the basal margin, and it is scarcely evident on one. The elytral fasciae vary from 
<number box="[217,254,1711,1737]" pageId="2" pageNumber="49" value="1.5">1.5</number>
X wide as long to 
<number box="[485,536,1711,1737]" pageId="2" pageNumber="49" value="0.67">0.67</number>
X wide as long, that of the largest 
<typeStatus box="[962,1063,1711,1737]" pageId="2" pageNumber="49">paratype</typeStatus>
closely matching the 
<typeStatus box="[1326,1432,1711,1737]" pageId="2" pageNumber="49">holotype</typeStatus>
, while the smaller specimens have the fasciae more quadrate, not projecting forward.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
